The paper deals with Markov chains on permutations, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of probabilities and the objective of identifying conditions for rapid mixing suggest that the paper may also belong to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of permutations and their properties is also relevant to graph theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
